SIMPLE LOGGING FACADE FOR JAVA (SLF4J)\
\
\
LOG4J\
- based on a named logger hierarchy\
- supports multiple appenders per logger\
- layered architecture\
\
How Log4j starts\
- by default the LogManager looks for a file called log4j.properties in the CLASSPATH\
- then it reads the root loggers level and the appender(s) attached to it, this is mostly the first line in the properties file\
- for each appender the appender type, appender layout and converstion pattern need to be specified\
- other than the root logger, other custom loggers can be defined with their own level and appender(s)\
\
Note: in the code it is important to specify\
\
Log4j appenders\
org.apache.log4j.ConsoleAppender\
org.apache.log4j.FileAppender\
