\
Log4j Components\
- loggers			-	responsible for capturing logging information\
- appenders		-	responsible for publishing logging information to various destinations\
- layouts			-	responsible for formatting logging information\
\
Log4j Objects\
- core objects			-	logger, layout, appender\
- support objects		-	level, filter, ObjectRenderer, LogManager\
\
\
Log4j Pattern\
%p		-	priority (aka level)\
%d		-	date				[ full format following d is \{yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS\} ]\
%t		-	method name\
%M		-	method name\
%c		-	absolute class name\
%m		-	the log message\
%L		-	line number in the log\
%F		-	class name\
%n		-	newline\
\
\
Log4j Levels/Priorities\
All\
Debug\
Info\
Warn\
Error\
Fatal\
Off		-	dont log anything\
\
Trace - where does this one fit?\
\
\
HOW TO LOG IN A PARTICULAR CLASS\
- use the LoggerFactory.getlogger() method to get a Logger object\
- log with info, debug, warning, error, fatal methods. }